==English==

===Adjectival phrase===
'''[[on]] the [[bubble]]'''

# {{autoracing}} Holding the last [[qualifying position]] with qualification still in progress, and thus liable to lose that position.
#: ''Smith was on the bubble but lost out when Jones was faster by a tenth of a second.''
# {{sports}} Having qualification for an event depend on the upcoming performances of other competitors.
#: ''The Nimrods had been on the bubble for the tournament, but played their way in by winning their last five games.''
# {{idiom}} Uncertain of success.
#: ''The new bond issue now appears to be on the bubble, with support eroding.''

